<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7456> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7456" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Aedile of the Plebs of uncertain date, who restored an early statue of the Sibyl near the Rostra (Plin. NH 34.22). Probably the tr. Pl. of 27, who devoted himself to Augustus (Macrob. Sat. 1.12.35-36; Dio 53.20.2-3), and carried the plebiscite to name the month Sextilis Augustus.\n" .
